Cody blinked, then shook his head. “Words fail,” he murmured, gingerly nudging the victorious Lulu to the side as he moved
towards the corpse. Lulu obligingly bounded out of the way, looking up at Cody as if for her next instructions. Cody
stopped and looked at her, frowning thoughtfully, but the idea forming in his head was lost when he noticed something on
the floor of the chamber behind Lulu. “Odd,” he said. “Looks like a statute of some kind – of a dog, or perhaps a jackal?”
Lulu paid it no attention, which had probably contributed to Cody's not noticing it before now.
